      <section>
        <h2>About Rio Miner</h2>
        <p>
          Rio Miner is designed for users who understand the risks of crypto mining and want to run 
          a <strong>real miner</strong> on their Android device. The app connects to a mining pool, 
          uses your device’s CPU/GPU, and reports hashrate, shares, and an on-chain wallet balance.
        </p>
        <p>
          Mining on a phone is <strong>not efficient</strong> and may not be profitable. 
          This app is intended for experimentation, hobby use, and demonstration only.
        </p>
        <div>
          <span class="tag">Real Mining</span>
          <span class="tag">High Resource Usage</span>
          <span class="tag">No Profit Guarantee</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Connects to a mining pool (you configure your pool/wallet details in the app)</li>
          <li>Displays hashrate, accepted shares, rejected shares, and uptime</li>
          <li>Shows on-chain wallet balance for the configured wallet address</li>
          <li>Mining status logs similar to desktop miner consoles</li>
          <li>Optional ad-supported features (e.g., UI themes, non-mining extras)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Risks &amp; Hardware Impact</h2>
        <p>
          Mining is a demanding workload. Before you use Rio Miner, please read and understand:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Mining can significantly increase <strong>battery drain</strong> and device temperature.</li>
          <li>Long sessions may cause <strong>hardware wear</strong> over time.</li>
          <li>Mining uses CPU/GPU resources and may slow down other apps.</li>
          <li>Mining can use your <strong>mobile data or Wi-Fi</strong>; charges may apply from your ISP.</li>
          <li>There is <strong>no guarantee of any earnings</strong> or profitability.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          By downloading and using the app, you accept full responsibility for any costs or damage 
          related to device usage, electricity, or data.
        </p>
      </section>

